A vintage 1950s illustration style scene showing a grand wooden postal sorting room with an elaborate mechanical contraption: brass gears, spinning wheels, and conveyor belts feeding hundreds of cream-colored envelopes through a central machine that stamps each one with a unique wax seal. Each envelope emerges personalized, floating down into organized mail slots. The machine has ornate Victorian-era details with copper pipes and glass tubes containing flowing ink in different colors. Warm amber lighting from hanging industrial lamps illuminates dust particles in the air. A single operator in period-appropriate attire adjusts dials on a control panel covered in switches and gauges. The envelopes fan out in a mesmerizing pattern, each slightly different from the last, suggesting mass customization through elegant automation.
